description:
&lt;p&gt; This is a full-time, 37.5 hours per week, opportunity for secondment or fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled and experienced practitioner to provide team leadership to our therapy led multi-disciplinary team who provide therapy and medical support to a cohort of residents at Coastal Lodge, a bed based rehabilitation unit. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The team work in partnership with Tricuro who are the registered managers of the unit. Within the evolving Discharge to Assess model patients have dynamic rehabilitation goals identified, with the aim of maximising independence for return to the community. Patients have a variety of needs, often with a significant level of frailty. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As team leader the post holder would be required to fully engage with MDT liaison, and consultant led MDT discussions to progress rehabilitation goals. The team and the unit form a valuable part of the local community services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team includes Occupational and Physio therapists, therapy assistants, nurse and Advanced Practitioner.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:  Alison Tallant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:  Locality Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:  alison.tallant1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:  07890327342&lt;/p&gt;
